column5: I have seen fish called many names, walleye are pickerel, walleyed pike,   bass are hogs, pigs, big puppies etc.  so I heard pike were called gators by a lot of people too, so heres a big gator I caught (on camera)    can we use the 120 inches for our team, as we kinda look like we are in a crappy spot on the standings
Sure, and how many inches do you want for the rare "shelled panfish" in the background?

thats a good one,, I missed that "rare breed" I didn't get close enough to measure but I guess we'll take 7 inches. I suppose you could check with my team captain to see if he'll go along with that guestimate.  Just thought I'd brighten your day LOL
I will vote yes if you enter it with the tape measure and sign in place.....   Art
LOL....Be sure to catch the measuring on video, I'm sure it'll go viral.
I don't know - maybe if we get a snap shot of bucket mouth being held open?
